klass.description: the class of the object to create

file.description: the file-like object to pickle to

f.description: the file-like object to unpickle from

path.description: string, (required), path of the file in the repository

content.description: string, (required), the actual data in the file

branch.description: string, (optional), branch to create the commit on. Defaults to the default branch of the repository

committer.description: InputGitAuthor, (optional), if no information is given the authenticated user's information will be used. You must specify both a name and email.

author.description: InputGitAuthor, (optional), if omitted this will be filled in with committer information. If passed, you must specify both a name and email.

sha.description: string, Required. The blob SHA of the file being replaced.

branch.description: string. The branch name. Default: the repository’s default branch (usually master)

author.description: InputGitAuthor, (optional), if omitted this will be filled in with committer information. If passed, you must specify both a name and email.

archived.description: bool. Unarchiving repositories is currently not supported through API (https://developer.github.com/v3/repos/#edit)

per.description: string, must be one of day or week, day by default

state.description: string. `open`, `closed`, or `all`. If this is not set the GitHub API default behavior will be used. At the moment this is to return only open issues. This might change anytime on GitHub API side and it could be clever to explicitly specify the state value.
